#money.hidden
    .ui.container(style="width: 85%;")
        .limit(style="padding: 0;")
            h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
                .content
                    i.book.icon
                    | Red Flag 8: Money Pickup
            .ui.centered.stackable.grid
                .eight.wide.column
                    p If the caller claims they will <b>quickly send someone to your home to pick up the money, do no comply</b>. Regardless of how they try to legitimize it by calling that person an 'officer,' 'government delivery person,' or any other official title, it is definitely a grandparent scam. 
                    p
                        em Do not send any money.


                    .callout
                        .dark-blue-square
                            img(src=user.avatarImg, alt='avatar picture')
                        .light-blue-content
                            h3.call-header Important
                            p No legitimate government agency will demand money over the phone.
                            p

                .eight.wide.column
                    div.ui.header
                        i.phone.volume.icon
                        | Example
                    //- a(href='https://dart-store.s3.amazonaws.com/grandparent-audio/randy.mp3' target='_blank') Listen to the audio example
                    .text-only-audio
                        ul
                            li.speaker2 Scammer: Grandma, I need you to do something for me. Can you withdraw some cash for someone to pick up and deliver to me? I need it right away.
                            li.speaker1 Grandparent: Yes, yes, of course. How much do you need?
                            li.speaker2 Scammer: It's $2,000, Grandma. Can you have it ready for pickup as soon as possible?
                            li.speaker1 Grandparent: Yes, yes, I'll get it ready right away. Where should I bring it to you?
                            li.speaker2 Scammer: I'll arrange for someone to come, Grandma. Just have the money ready. And please don't tell Mom and Dad about this, okay? They'll only worry, and I don't want to stress them out more than they already are.
